articles.description: Wednesday's Big Ten game between No. 22 Michigan and Iowa will feature the best versus the worst in the conference in one important aspect.
articles.headline: No. 22 Michigan brings stout defense into Iowa game

articles.description: The Razorbacks finish with four players in double figures and hold the Rebels to 29 percent from the floor in the win.
articles.headline: Arkansas downs Ole Miss 75-64

images.caption: The Razorbacks finish with four players in double figures and hold the Rebels to 29 percent from the floor in the win.
images.name: Arkansas downs Ole Miss 75-64

articles.description: Jared Terrell gets the lob from Jeff Dowtin and slams it home with two hands for the Rams.
articles.headline: URI's Terrell climbs ladder for alley-oop

images.caption: Jared Terrell gets the lob from Jeff Dowtin and slams it home with two hands for the Rams.

articles.description: Fourth-ranked Xavier will try to extend its winning streak to nine games and maintain its slim hold on first place in the Big East Conference on Wednesday night when the Musketeers welcome Seton Hall to the Cintas Center.
articles.headline: Xavier's 4 Musketeers seek ninth straight victory

articles.description: Daniel Gafford scored 19 points to lead four Arkansas players in double figures Tuesday night as the Razorbacks defeated Mississippi 75-64.
articles.headline: Gafford, Hall lead Arkansas past Ole Miss, 75-64

images.caption: The Razorbacks finish with four players in double figures and hold the Rebels to 29 percent from the floor in the win.
images.name: Arkansas downs Ole Miss 75-64

articles.description: Antwon Lillard sank three free throws after he was fouled on a 3-point attempt in the final seconds and Bowling Green rallied to beat Western Michigan 83-81 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Lillard sinks late FTs, Bowling Green rallies for 83-81 win
